divs: sighting detailsim 21 years old and i live in currambine which is a suburb about 35min north of the city of perth, western australia. i was sitting down watching television and for some reason i just decided to head out the back and catch a photo of the sunsetting(only with my iphone, im not a photographer). after taking the shot i looked at the photo and this extra translucent anomaly appeared in the photo which was not visible in the sky? at first i thought i had just captured a comet\meteor but when i transfered the photo onto my macbook it looks like something more. there are 4 distinctively brighter "dots" and they are relatively uniform in seperation?
Summary: Anomaly was captured by camera(accidentally) when I was taking a picture of the sunset, NOT VISIBLE TO THE EYE?
